{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/regexref"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a compiled form of a regular expression."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","title":"RegexRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"RegexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib8RegexRefV","symbolKind":"struct","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"RegexRef","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Structure","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"RegexRef","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After instantiating a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", you can use its methods to find matches","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in a string, replace matches within a string, or split the string at matches."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" implements regular expression pattern matching using syntax and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"semantics (such as character classes, quantifiers, and capture groups)","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"similar to Perl regular expression. See the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"man:pcre2pattern(3)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A typical scenario for regex pattern matching is to check if a string"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"matches a pattern. The following statements implement this scenario.","type":"text"}]},{"code":["const char *regex_pattern = \".*GLib.*\";","const char *string_to_search = \"You will love the GLib implementation of regex\";","`g_autoptr(GMatchInfo)` match_info = NULL;","`g_autoptr(GRegex)` regex = NULL;","","regex = g_regex_new (regex_pattern, G_REGEX_DEFAULT, G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT, NULL);","g_assert (regex != NULL);","","if (g_regex_match (regex, string_to_search, G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT, &match_info))","  {","    int start_pos, end_pos;","    g_match_info_fetch_pos (match_info, 0, &start_pos, &end_pos);","    g_print (\"Match successful! Overall pattern matches bytes `d` to `d`\\n\", start_pos, end_pos);","  }","else","  {","    g_print (\"No match!\\n\");","  }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"{ .c }"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The constructor for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" includes two sets of bitmapped flags:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"[flags","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexCompileFlags","isActive":true},{"text":"]—These flags","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"control how GLib compiles the regex. There are options for case"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sensitivity, multiline, ignoring whitespace, etc.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"[flags","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexMatchFlags","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"]—These flags control"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"text":"’s matching behavior, such as anchoring and customizing definitions","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"for newline characters.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some regex patterns include backslash assertions, such as "},{"code":"\\d","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (digit) or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\\D","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (non-digit). The regex pattern must escape those backslashes. For"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"example, the pattern ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\"\\\\d\\\\D\""},{"type":"text","text":" matches a digit followed by a non-digit."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GLib’s implementation of pattern matching includes a "},{"code":"start_position","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"argument for some of the match, replace, and split methods. Specifying"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a start position provides flexibility when you want to ignore the first"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" characters of a string, but want to incorporate backslash assertions","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at character ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"n"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" - 1. For example, a database field contains inconsistent"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"spelling for a job title: ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"healthcare provider"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"health-care provider"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The database manager wants to make the spelling consistent by adding a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"hyphen when it is missing. The following regex pattern tests for the string","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"care"},{"type":"text","text":" preceded by a non-word boundary character (instead of a hyphen)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and followed by a space."}]},{"syntax":"{ .c }","type":"codeListing","code":["const char *regex_pattern = \"\\\\Bcare\\\\s\";"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An efficient way to match with this pattern is to start examining at","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"start_position"},{"type":"text","text":" 6 in the string "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"healthcare"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"health-care"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"{ .c }","code":["const char *regex_pattern = \"\\\\Bcare\\\\s\";","const char *string_to_search = \"healthcare provider\";","`g_autoptr(GMatchInfo)` match_info = NULL;","`g_autoptr(GRegex)` regex = NULL;","","regex = g_regex_new (","  regex_pattern,","  G_REGEX_DEFAULT,","  G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT,","  NULL);","g_assert (regex != NULL);","","g_regex_match_full (","  regex,","  string_to_search,","  -1,","  6, \/\/ position of 'c' in the test string.","  G_REGEX_MATCH_DEFAULT,","  &match_info,","  NULL);"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The method [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Regex.match_full"},{"type":"text","text":"] (and other methods implementing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"start_pos"},{"text":") allow for lookback before the start position to determine if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the previous character satisfies an assertion.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Unless you set the [flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexCompileFlags.RAW","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] as one of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegexCompileFlags"},{"type":"text","text":", all the strings passed to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" methods must"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be encoded in UTF-8. The lengths and the positions inside the strings are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in bytes and not in characters, so, for instance, "},{"code":"\\xc3\\xa0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (i.e., "},{"code":"à","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is two bytes long but it is treated as a single character. If you set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_REGEX_RAW"},{"text":", the strings can be non-valid UTF-8 strings and a byte is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"treated as a character, so ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\xc3\\xa0"},{"text":" is two bytes and two characters long.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Regarding line endings, "},{"code":"\\n","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" matches a "},{"code":"\\n","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" character, and "},{"code":"\\r","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" matches","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\r"},{"text":" character. More generally, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\R"},{"text":" matches all typical line endings:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"CR + LF ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\r\\n"},{"type":"text","text":"), LF (linefeed, U+000A, "},{"code":"\\n","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), VT (vertical tab, U+000B,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\v"},{"type":"text","text":"), FF (formfeed, U+000C, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\f"},{"text":"), CR (carriage return, U+000D, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\r"},{"text":"),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"NEL (next line, U+0085), LS (line separator, U+2028), and PS (paragraph","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"separator, U+2029).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The behaviour of the dot, circumflex, and dollar metacharacters are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"affected by newline characters. By default, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"type":"text","text":" matches any newline"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"character matched by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\\R"},{"type":"text","text":". You can limit the matched newline characters by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specifying the [flags","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CR"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_LF","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CRLF"},{"type":"text","text":"] compile options, and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with [flags","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_ANY"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CR"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_LF","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.RegexMatchFlags.NEWLINE_CRLF"},{"text":"] match options.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"These settings are also relevant when compiling a pattern if"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[flags"},{"code":"GLib.RegexCompileFlags.EXTENDED","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] is set and an unescaped"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"text":" outside a character class is encountered. This indicates a comment","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that lasts until after the next newline."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Because "},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" does not modify its internal state between creation and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"destruction, you can create and modify the same ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"different threads. In contrast, [struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MatchInfo"},{"type":"text","text":"] is not thread safe."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The regular expression low-level functionalities are obtained through"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the excellent ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/www.pcre.org\/"},{"text":" library written by Philip Hazel.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef"},{"text":" only as an ","type":"text"},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GRegex"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Regex"},{"text":" (instead of ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef"},{"text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GRegex","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}],"name":"Note"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(_:)-1hgnb","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(_:)-1vppv","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(_:)-2yoe7","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(_:)-51y4h","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(_:)-7dujh","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(mutating:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/init(pattern:compileOptions:matchOptions:)"],"title":"Initializers","anchor":"Initializers"},{"title":"Instance Properties","anchor":"Instance-Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/ptr"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","anchor":"Default-Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/PointerWrapper-Implementations","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/RegexRef\/RegexProtocol-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"relationshipsSectio